C++ LIBRARIES
+++++++++++++

The ROK4 server, BE4 tools and IMAGE library require these extern C++ libraries. Equivalent debian package name and centos package name are given.

* external, dynamically linked
    - LIB NAME | DEBIAN | CENTOS
    - TINYXML | libtinyxml-dev | 
    - ZLIB | zlib1g-dev | 
    - TIFF | libtiff5-dev | 
    - PNG | libpng16-dev | 
    - CURL | libcurl4-openssl-dev | 
    - OPENSSL | libssl-dev | 
    - TURBOJPEG | libturbojpeg | 
    - JPEG | libjpeg | 
    - KAKADU -> proprietary software, no package
    	 or
    - OPENJPEG | libopenjp2-7-dev | 
         
         if BUILD_OBJECT=TRUE    
    - RADOS | librados-dev | 
    - HIREDIS | libhiredis-dev | 

* external, statically linked
    - PTHREAD | libc6-dev | 

* internal, statically linked
    - PROJ
    - UNITTEST
    - FCGI
    - LZW
    - PKB
    - LOGGER
    - IMAGE

PERL LIBRARIES
++++++++++++++

The BE4 tools require these extern perl libraries. Equivalent debian package name are given if exists.

    Cwd -> perl-base
    Data::Dumper -> libperl5.22
    Digest::SHA -> libperl5.22 or libdigest-sha-perl
    ExtUtils::MakeMaker -> perl-modules-5.22
    File::Basename -> perl-base
    File::Copy -> perl-base
    File::Map -> use CPAN
    File::Path -> perl-base
    File::Spec -> perl-base
#    File::Spec::Link -> libfile-copy-link-perl
    FindBin -> perl-modules-5.22
    Geo::GDAL -> libgdal-perl
    Geo::OGR -> libgdal-perl
    Geo::OSR -> libgdal-perl
    Getopt::Long -> perl-base
    HTTP::Request -> libhttp-message-perl
    HTTP::Response -> libhttp-message-perl
    List::Util -> perl-base
    Log::Log4perl -> liblog-log4perl-perl
    LWP::UserAgent -> libwww-perl
    Math::BigFloat -> perl-modules-5.22 or libmath-bigint-perl
    POSIX -> perl-base
    Scalar::Util -> perl-base
    Test::More -> perl-modules-5.22
    Tie::File -> perl-modules-5.22
    Tk -> perl-tk
    Tk::EntryCheck -> use CPAN
    Tk::FileSelect -> perl-tk
    Tk::LabFrame -> perl-tk
    Tk::NoteBook -> perl-tk
    Tk::ROText -> perl-tk
    Tk::Table -> perl-tk
#    XML::Hash -> use CPAN
    XML::LibXML -> libxml-libxml-perl

So packages list is

    libfile-copy-link-perl
    libgdal-perl
    libhttp-message-perl
    liblog-log4perl-perl
    libperl5.22
    libdigest-sha-perl
    libwww-perl
    libxml-libxml-perl
    perl-base
    perl-modules-5.22
    libmath-bigint-perl
    perl-tk

This two commands should be enough:

    apt install libfile-copy-link-perl libgdal-perl libhttp-message-perl liblog-log4perl-perl libperl5.22 libperl5.22 libdigest-sha-perl libwww-perl libxml-libxml-perl perl-base perl-modules-5.22 perl-modules-5.22 libmath-bigint-perl perl-tk

#    cpan Tk::EntryCheck File::Map XML::Hash

The perl libraries list can be obtained with the command grep -r "^use [A-Z]" pyramide/ | cut -d' ' -f 2 | grep -v COMMON | grep -v BE4 | grep -v JOINCACHE | grep -v WMTSALAD | grep -v PYR2PYR | sed "s#;##" | sed "s# ##" | sort | uniq

To find the package equivalent, for the lib Foo::Bar for example, we can first search 'libfoo-bar-perl' and if not exists, use the tool 'apt-file' and execute 'apt-list search Foo/Bar.pm'

To know where libraries are searched, execute 'env -i perl -V' and see and look the @INC section :

  @INC:
    /etc/perl
    /usr/local/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl/5.22.1
    /usr/local/share/perl/5.22.1
    /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl5/5.22
    /usr/share/perl5
    /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl/5.22
    /usr/share/perl/5.22
    /usr/local/lib/site_perl
    /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl-base
    .

To test if all dependencies are satisfied, play a script with this content:

    use strict;
    use warnings;
    use AutoLoader qw(AUTOLOAD);
    use Cwd;
    use Data::Dumper;
    use Digest::SHA;
    use ExtUtils::MakeMaker;
    use File::Basename;
    use File::Copy;
    use File::Map qw(map_file);
    use File::Path;
    use File::Path qw(make_path);
    use File::Spec ;
    use File::Spec;
#    use File::Spec::Link;
    use FindBin qw($Bin);
    use Geo::GDAL;
    use Geo::OGR;
    use Geo::OSR;
    use Getopt::Long;
    use HTTP::Request;
    use HTTP::Response;
    use List::Util qw(min max);
    use Log::Log4perl qw(:easy);
    use LWP::UserAgent;
    use Math::BigFloat;
    use POSIX qw(locale_h);
    use Scalar::Util qw/reftype/;
    use Test::More;
    use Tie::File;
    use Tk;
    use Tk::EntryCheck;
    use Tk::FileSelect;
    use Tk::LabFrame;
    use Tk::NoteBook;
    use Tk::ROText;
    use Tk::Table;
#    use XML::Hash;
    use XML::LibXML;
